      "content": "It's mostly about efficiency and resource management. Maintaining separate specialized models is a lot more computationally expensive than having one massive, multi-purpose model that can handle everything. As for performance, the lab believes the general reasoning capabilities of the new model will actually make it more robust, even if it loses your specific specialized tuning. It's just the way the project is evolving.",
